        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/0/0/d002c517784078b5834f12efe45ad224596f75ad.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/1/6/1169b5ab2cbc837edbec8298a9a56d23dfedca02.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> be two circles intersecting at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/8/6/9866e3a998d628ba0941eb4fea0666ac391d149a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$Q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"13\" height=\"16\" />. The common tangent, closer to <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />, of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/0/0/d002c517784078b5834f12efe45ad224596f75ad.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/1/6/1169b5ab2cbc837edbec8298a9a56d23dfedca02.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> touches <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/0/0/d002c517784078b5834f12efe45ad224596f75ad.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/1/9/019e9892786e493964e145e7c5cf7b700314e53b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A$\" width=\"13\" height=\"13\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/1/6/1169b5ab2cbc837edbec8298a9a56d23dfedca02.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/f/5/ff5fb3d775862e2123b007eb4373ff6cc1a34d4e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$B$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />. The tangent of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/0/0/d002c517784078b5834f12efe45ad224596f75ad.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" /> meets <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/1/6/1169b5ab2cbc837edbec8298a9a56d23dfedca02.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\Gamma_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"17\" height=\"15\" /> at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/3/3/c3355896da590fc491a10150a50416687626d7cc.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$C$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />, which is different from <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/b/4/4b4cade9ca8a2c8311fafcf040bc5b15ca507f52.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$P$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />, and the extension of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/3/b/e3bb4eeb347e74e025fd175c22f1f7275af0555e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AP$\" width=\"27\" height=\"13\" /> meets <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/c/5/6c52a41dcbd739f1d026c5d4f181438b75b76976.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BC$\" width=\"28\" height=\"12\" /> at <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/f/f/eff43e84f8a3bcf7b6965f0a3248bc4d3a9d0cd4.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$R$\" width=\"14\" height=\"12\" />.\nProve that the circumcircle of triangle <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/1/c/91c587b0c1e5de0bde79b9d8c36913c16dee04d9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$PQR$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"42\" height=\"16\" /> is tangent to <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/8/7/f874b39870586f0504f50a667f2bafedddf47904.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BP$\" width=\"28\" height=\"12\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/1/e/b1e13b02d52b38e131b0952f60238edfda7640a0.png\